## What's there

A runnable Node.js/Express + SQLite DevOps dashboard:

- **Auth & roles** â€” register/login, `viewer` (read-only) and `operator` (manage own services + deploy).
- **Services** â€” operators register services with repo URL, description, and an ordered list of shell deployment steps.
- **Deployments** â€” steps run sequentially via `child_process` (non-zero exit aborts), with per-service secrets injected as env vars and a 10-min per-step timeout.
- **Logs** â€” streamed live to the browser over **SSE** and persisted line-by-line in the DB for later replay.
- **Secrets** â€” encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM), write-only from the UI (values never rendered back).

## How the security requirements are met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| SQL injection | better-sqlite3 **prepared statements + bound params** everywhere (`src/models/*`) |
| Password hashing | **bcrypt** (`bcryptjs`, cost 12) + constant-time dummy-hash compare to avoid user enumeration |
| Input validation | `express-validator` allow-lists (role/URL/secret-key regex), body size caps (`src/lib/validators.js`) |
| XSS | EJS auto-escaping (`<%= %>`), client logs via `textContent` only, strict **CSP with no inline JS/CSS** |
| CSRF | Synchronizer token in session, constant-time check on all mutating requests (`src/middleware/csrf.js`) |
| Access control / IDOR | `requireOwnership` re-loads the resource and checks `owner_id === user.id`; missing â†’ 404, not 403 (`src/routes/services.js`) |
| Session cookies | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in prod; session regenerated on login/register (fixation) |
| Security headers | Helmet (CSP, HSTS, no-referrer, frame-ancestors none, nosniff) |
| Error leakage | Central handler logs server-side, returns generic messages only |
| No hardcoded secrets | All from env; prod refuses to boot without `SESSION_SECRET`/`SECRETS_KEY`; `.env` git-ignored |

Run instructions are in `README.md` (`npm install`, copy `.env.example`â†’`.env`, `npm start`, port 5100).

